{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017DkggvmZniyrKy9kkTdT9T","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 4.3: Trace ID Generation & Injection\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want trace IDs generated per iteration and injected into prompts,\n9\tso that agent activity correlates to observability data.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a trace ID generator module at `src/lib/trace-id.ts`\n14\t   **When** inspected\n15\t   **Then** it exports a `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` function\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** an iteration starting with runId `abc123`, iteration `2`, and taskName `verify`\n19\t   **When** `generateTraceId()` is called\n20\t   **Then** the returned string matches the format `ch-abc123-2-verify` (pattern: `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`)\n21\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t3. **Given** a `generateTraceId()` call with a runId containing special characters (spaces, slashes, unicode)\n24\t   **When** the trace ID is generated\n25\t   **Then** special characters are sanitized (replaced with hyphens or stripped) so the trace ID is safe for use in logs, metrics labels, and HTTP headers\n26\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t4. **Given** a generated trace ID\n29\t   **When** it is formatted for injection via `formatTracePrompt(traceId: string): string`\n30\t   **Then** it returns a system prompt fragment containing the trace ID in a structured block (e.g., `[TRACE] trace_id=ch-abc123-2-verify`) that an agent can include in log/metric/trace output\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t5. **Given** the `formatTracePrompt()` output\n34\t   **When** passed as `appendSystemPrompt` to `dispatchAgent()` (via `DispatchOptions`)\n35\t   **Then** it is appended to the agent's system prompt (verified by confirming `agent-dispatch.ts` line 123-124 already handles `appendSystemPrompt`)\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t6. **Given** a trace ID generated during a dispatch\n39\t   **When** it is recorded in workflow state via `recordTraceId(traceId: string, state: WorkflowState): WorkflowState`\n40\t   **Then** the returned state has the trace ID appended to a `trace_ids: string[]` array on the `WorkflowState` object\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t7. **Given** a `WorkflowState` with `trace_ids` persisted to `workflow-state.yaml`\n44\t   **When** `readWorkflowState()` reads it back\n45\t   **Then** the `trace_ids` array is correctly deserialized and accessible\n46\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t8. **Given** multiple iterations in a workflow run\n49\t   **When** each iteration generates and records a trace ID\n50\t   **Then** `workflow-state.yaml` contains all trace IDs in order (one per dispatch call)\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t9. **Given** unit tests for trace ID generation and injection\n54\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n55\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for the trace ID module covering: format correctness, sanitization of special characters, prompt fragment formatting, trace ID recording in state, round-trip persistence, and multiple iteration accumulation\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n59\t\n60\t- [x] Task 1: Create trace ID generator module (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n61\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/trace-id.ts`\n62\t  - [x] Implement `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` — produces `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n63\t  - [x] Implement `sanitizeSegment(segment: string): string` — replaces non-alphanumeric characters (except hyphens) with hyphens, collapses consecutive hyphens, trims leading/trailing hyphens\n64\t  - [x] Apply sanitization to `runId` and `taskName` segments\n65\t\n66\t- [x] Task 2: Create prompt injection formatter (AC: #4, #5)\n67\t  - [x] Implement `formatTracePrompt(traceId: string): string` — returns a structured system prompt fragment like:\n68\t    ```\n69\t    [TRACE] trace_id={traceId}\n70\t    Include this trace ID in all log output, metric labels, and trace spans for correlation.\n71\t    ```\n72\t  - [x] Verify that `agent-dispatch.ts` already handles `appendSystemPrompt` (it does — lines 121-125)\n73\t  - [x] No changes needed to `agent-dispatch.ts` — it already supports this via `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt`\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 3: Add trace_ids to WorkflowState (AC: #6, #7)\n76\t  - [x] Add `trace_ids?: string[]` to `WorkflowState` interface in `workflow-state.ts`\n77\t  - [x] Update `getDefaultWorkflowState()` to include `trace_ids: []`\n78\t  - [x] Update `isValidWorkflowState()` to validate `trace_ids` as optional array of strings\n79\t  - [x] Implement `recordTraceId(traceId: string, state: WorkflowState): WorkflowState` in `trace-id.ts` — returns new state with trace ID appended to `trace_ids` array (immutable)\n80\t\n81\t- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #9)\n82\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts`\n83\t  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('abc123', 2, 'verify')` returns `'ch-abc123-2-verify'`\n84\t  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('run with spaces', 1, 'implement')` sanitizes to `'ch-run-with-spaces-1-implement'`\n85\t  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('a/b\\\\c', 0, 'd.e')` sanitizes slashes, backslashes, dots\n86\t  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('', 1, 'verify')` handles empty runId gracefully\n87\t  - [x] Test: `formatTracePrompt('ch-abc-1-dev')` returns string containing `trace_id=ch-abc-1-dev`\n88\t  - [x] Test: `formatTracePrompt('ch-abc-1-dev')` includes instruction text about including trace ID in logs\n89\t  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId('ch-abc-1-dev', state)` appends to trace_ids array\n90\t  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId` does not mutate the input state\n91\t  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId` throws on empty traceId\n92\t  - [x] Test: round-trip — write state with trace_ids, read it back, array matches\n93\t  - [x] Test: multiple `recordTraceId` calls accumulate trace IDs in order\n94\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on `trace-id.ts`\n95\t\n96\t## Dev Notes\n97\t\n98\t### Module Design Decision\n99\t\n100\tTrace ID generation is a standalone `trace-id.ts` module rather than being added to `agent-dispatch.ts` or `session-manager.ts`. Rationale:\n101\t\n102\t1. `agent-dispatch.ts` is intentionally stateless — it does not import `workflow-state` (per story 4-1 anti-patterns)\n103\t2. `session-manager.ts` handles session boundary concerns, not observability — separate concern\n104\t3. The workflow-engine (story 5-1) orchestrates: generate trace ID -> format prompt -> dispatch agent -> record trace ID -> write state\n105\t\n106\t### How Trace IDs Work End-to-End\n107\t\n108\t```\n109\tworkflow-engine (story 5-1) calls:\n110\t  1. generateTraceId(runId, iteration, taskName)\n111\t     -> returns 'ch-abc123-2-verify'\n112\t  2. formatTracePrompt(traceId)\n113\t     -> returns prompt fragment with [TRACE] block\n114\t  3. dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, { appendSystemPrompt: tracePrompt })\n115\t     -> agent-dispatch appends trace to system prompt (already implemented, line 123-124)\n116\t  4. recordTraceId(traceId, currentState)\n117\t     -> returns updated state with trace ID in trace_ids array\n118\t  5. writeWorkflowState(updatedState)\n119\t     -> persisted to disk\n120\t```\n121\t\n122\t### Trace ID Format\n123\t\n124\tFormat: `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n125\t\n126\t- `ch` prefix: identifies this as a codeharness trace (avoids collision with other trace systems)\n127\t- `runId`: unique per workflow run (generated by engine, story 5-1)\n128\t- `iteration`: integer, zero-based iteration counter within the run\n129\t- `taskName`: the workflow task name (e.g., 'implement', 'verify', 'retry')\n130\t\n131\tAll segments are sanitized to be safe for: log grep, metrics labels (Prometheus-compatible), HTTP headers (W3C Trace Context compatible character set), and YAML serialization.\n132\t\n133\t### Existing Code That Already Supports This\n134\t\n135\t- `agent-dispatch.ts` lines 14-15: `appendSystemPrompt?: string` in `DispatchOptions` — forward-compat placeholder created in story 4-1\n136\t- `agent-dispatch.ts` lines 121-125: appends `appendSystemPrompt` to `definition.instructions` — already implemented\n137\t- `workflow-state.ts` `WorkflowState` interface: will be extended with `trace_ids?: string[]`\n138\t\n139\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n140\t\n141\t- Does NOT generate the `runId` — that's the workflow-engine's responsibility (story 5-1)\n142\t- Does NOT orchestrate when trace IDs are generated — that's the engine's loop (story 5-1)\n143\t- Does NOT implement OTLP trace propagation to observability backends — that's Epic 6 (evaluator observability)\n144\t- Does NOT modify `agent-dispatch.ts` — it already handles `appendSystemPrompt`\n145\t- Does NOT modify `session-manager.ts` — separate concern\n146\t\n147\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n148\t\n149\t- **Do NOT add workflow-state imports to agent-dispatch.ts** — keep dispatch stateless\n150\t- **Do NOT generate runId in trace-id.ts** — the engine owns run identity\n151\t- **Do NOT cache trace IDs in module-level variables** — always return new state objects for crash recovery safety\n152\t- **Do NOT mutate WorkflowState in place** — return new state objects from `recordTraceId()`\n153\t\n154\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n155\t\n156\t- **Story 4-1** created `agent-dispatch.ts` with `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt` — this module provides the formatted content for that field\n157\t- **Story 1-3** created `workflow-state.ts` with `WorkflowState` interface — this module extends it with `trace_ids`\n158\t- **Story 4-2** created `session-manager.ts` with the immutable state pattern — this module follows the same pattern\n159\t\n160\t### Project Structure Notes\n161\t\n162\t- New file: `src/lib/trace-id.ts` — trace ID generation, prompt formatting, state recording\n163\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts`\n164\t- Modified file: `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — add `trace_ids?: string[]` to `WorkflowState`, update default and validator\n165\t- Aligns with architecture pattern: each module in `src/lib/` is one file with co-located test\n166\t\n167\t### Testing Strategy\n168\t\n169\tUnit tests only — no file I/O mocking needed for the generator and formatter. For `recordTraceId`, test with in-memory `WorkflowState` objects (same pattern as `session-manager.ts`). For round-trip persistence, use the existing `writeWorkflowState`/`readWorkflowState` with a temp directory.\n170\t\n171\t### References\n172\t\n173\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 4.3: Trace ID Generation & Injection]\n174\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-dispatch]\n175\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#FR36-37 — Observability, trace ID injection]\n176\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR22 — Trace ID per iteration]\n177\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR36 — Trace IDs correlate across iteration, prompt, logs, metrics, traces]\n178\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt, lines 14-15, 121-125]\n179\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState interface, TaskCheckpoint]\n180\t- [Source: src/lib/session-manager.ts — immutable state pattern reference]\n181\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration.md — predecessor story]\n182\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md — predecessor story]\n183\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015-85c3-0be0521b6265","uuid":"ec981e35-5eaa-47da-a147-2ce135b1e946","timestamp":"2026-04-02T20:56:15.326Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-3-trace-id-generation-injection.md","content":"# Story 4.3: Trace ID Generation & Injection\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want trace IDs generated per iteration and injected into prompts,\nso that agent activity correlates to observability data.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a trace ID generator module at `src/lib/trace-id.ts`\n   **When** inspected\n   **Then** it exports a `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` function\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** an iteration starting with runId `abc123`, iteration `2`, and taskName `verify`\n   **When** `generateTraceId()` is called\n   **Then** the returned string matches the format `ch-abc123-2-verify` (pattern: `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a `generateTraceId()` call with a runId containing special characters (spaces, slashes, unicode)\n   **When** the trace ID is generated\n   **Then** special characters are sanitized (replaced with hyphens or stripped) so the trace ID is safe for use in logs, metrics labels, and HTTP headers\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a generated trace ID\n   **When** it is formatted for injection via `formatTracePrompt(traceId: string): string`\n   **Then** it returns a system prompt fragment containing the trace ID in a structured block (e.g., `[TRACE] trace_id=ch-abc123-2-verify`) that an agent can include in log/metric/trace output\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** the `formatTracePrompt()` output\n   **When** passed as `appendSystemPrompt` to `dispatchAgent()` (via `DispatchOptions`)\n   **Then** it is appended to the agent's system prompt (verified by confirming `agent-dispatch.ts` line 123-124 already handles `appendSystemPrompt`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a trace ID generated during a dispatch\n   **When** it is recorded in workflow state via `recordTraceId(traceId: string, state: WorkflowState): WorkflowState`\n   **Then** the returned state has the trace ID appended to a `trace_ids: string[]` array on the `WorkflowState` object\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** a `WorkflowState` with `trace_ids` persisted to `workflow-state.yaml`\n   **When** `readWorkflowState()` reads it back\n   **Then** the `trace_ids` array is correctly deserialized and accessible\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** multiple iterations in a workflow run\n   **When** each iteration generates and records a trace ID\n   **Then** `workflow-state.yaml` contains all trace IDs in order (one per dispatch call)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** unit tests for trace ID generation and injection\n   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for the trace ID module covering: format correctness, sanitization of special characters, prompt fragment formatting, trace ID recording in state, round-trip persistence, and multiple iteration accumulation\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Create trace ID generator module (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/trace-id.ts`\n  - [x] Implement `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` — produces `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n  - [x] Implement `sanitizeSegment(segment: string): string` — replaces non-alphanumeric characters (except hyphens) with hyphens, collapses consecutive hyphens, trims leading/trailing hyphens\n  - [x] Apply sanitization to `runId` and `taskName` segments\n\n- [x] Task 2: Create prompt injection formatter (AC: #4, #5)\n  - [x] Implement `formatTracePrompt(traceId: string): string` — returns a structured system prompt fragment like:\n    ```\n    [TRACE] trace_id={traceId}\n    Include this trace ID in all log output, metric labels, and trace spans for correlation.\n    ```\n  - [x] Verify that `agent-dispatch.ts` already handles `appendSystemPrompt` (it does — lines 121-125)\n  - [x] No changes needed to `agent-dispatch.ts` — it already supports this via `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt`\n\n- [x] Task 3: Add trace_ids to WorkflowState (AC: #6, #7)\n  - [x] Add `trace_ids?: string[]` to `WorkflowState` interface in `workflow-state.ts`\n  - [x] Update `getDefaultWorkflowState()` to include `trace_ids: []`\n  - [x] Update `isValidWorkflowState()` to validate `trace_ids` as optional array of strings\n  - [x] Implement `recordTraceId(traceId: string, state: WorkflowState): WorkflowState` in `trace-id.ts` — returns new state with trace ID appended to `trace_ids` array (immutable)\n\n- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #9)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts`\n  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('abc123', 2, 'verify')` returns `'ch-abc123-2-verify'`\n  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('run with spaces', 1, 'implement')` sanitizes to `'ch-run-with-spaces-1-implement'`\n  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('a/b\\\\c', 0, 'd.e')` sanitizes slashes, backslashes, dots\n  - [x] Test: `generateTraceId('', 1, 'verify')` handles empty runId gracefully\n  - [x] Test: `formatTracePrompt('ch-abc-1-dev')` returns string containing `trace_id=ch-abc-1-dev`\n  - [x] Test: `formatTracePrompt('ch-abc-1-dev')` includes instruction text about including trace ID in logs\n  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId('ch-abc-1-dev', state)` appends to trace_ids array\n  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId` does not mutate the input state\n  - [x] Test: `recordTraceId` throws on empty traceId\n  - [x] Test: round-trip — write state with trace_ids, read it back, array matches\n  - [x] Test: multiple `recordTraceId` calls accumulate trace IDs in order\n  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on `trace-id.ts`\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Module Design Decision\n\nTrace ID generation is a standalone `trace-id.ts` module rather than being added to `agent-dispatch.ts` or `session-manager.ts`. Rationale:\n\n1. `agent-dispatch.ts` is intentionally stateless — it does not import `workflow-state` (per story 4-1 anti-patterns)\n2. `session-manager.ts` handles session boundary concerns, not observability — separate concern\n3. The workflow-engine (story 5-1) orchestrates: generate trace ID -> format prompt -> dispatch agent -> record trace ID -> write state\n\n### How Trace IDs Work End-to-End\n\n```\nworkflow-engine (story 5-1) calls:\n  1. generateTraceId(runId, iteration, taskName)\n     -> returns 'ch-abc123-2-verify'\n  2. formatTracePrompt(traceId)\n     -> returns prompt fragment with [TRACE] block\n  3. dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, { appendSystemPrompt: tracePrompt })\n     -> agent-dispatch appends trace to system prompt (already implemented, line 123-124)\n  4. recordTraceId(traceId, currentState)\n     -> returns updated state with trace ID in trace_ids array\n  5. writeWorkflowState(updatedState)\n     -> persisted to disk\n```\n\n### Trace ID Format\n\nFormat: `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n\n- `ch` prefix: identifies this as a codeharness trace (avoids collision with other trace systems)\n- `runId`: unique per workflow run (generated by engine, story 5-1)\n- `iteration`: integer, zero-based iteration counter within the run\n- `taskName`: the workflow task name (e.g., 'implement', 'verify', 'retry')\n\nAll segments are sanitized to be safe for: log grep, metrics labels (Prometheus-compatible), HTTP headers (W3C Trace Context compatible character set), and YAML serialization.\n\n### Existing Code That Already Supports This\n\n- `agent-dispatch.ts` lines 14-15: `appendSystemPrompt?: string` in `DispatchOptions` — forward-compat placeholder created in story 4-1\n- `agent-dispatch.ts` lines 121-125: appends `appendSystemPrompt` to `definition.instructions` — already implemented\n- `workflow-state.ts` `WorkflowState` interface: will be extended with `trace_ids?: string[]`\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Do\n\n- Does NOT generate the `runId` — that's the workflow-engine's responsibility (story 5-1)\n- Does NOT orchestrate when trace IDs are generated — that's the engine's loop (story 5-1)\n- Does NOT implement OTLP trace propagation to observability backends — that's Epic 6 (evaluator observability)\n- Does NOT modify `agent-dispatch.ts` — it already handles `appendSystemPrompt`\n- Does NOT modify `session-manager.ts` — separate concern\n\n### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n\n- **Do NOT add workflow-state imports to agent-dispatch.ts** — keep dispatch stateless\n- **Do NOT generate runId in trace-id.ts** — the engine owns run identity\n- **Do NOT cache trace IDs in module-level variables** — always return new state objects for crash recovery safety\n- **Do NOT mutate WorkflowState in place** — return new state objects from `recordTraceId()`\n\n### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n\n- **Story 4-1** created `agent-dispatch.ts` with `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt` — this module provides the formatted content for that field\n- **Story 1-3** created `workflow-state.ts` with `WorkflowState` interface — this module extends it with `trace_ids`\n- **Story 4-2** created `session-manager.ts` with the immutable state pattern — this module follows the same pattern\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New file: `src/lib/trace-id.ts` — trace ID generation, prompt formatting, state recording\n- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts`\n- Modified file: `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — add `trace_ids?: string[]` to `WorkflowState`, update default and validator\n- Aligns with architecture pattern: each module in `src/lib/` is one file with co-located test\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\nUnit tests only — no file I/O mocking needed for the generator and formatter. For `recordTraceId`, test with in-memory `WorkflowState` objects (same pattern as `session-manager.ts`). For round-trip persistence, use the existing `writeWorkflowState`/`readWorkflowState` with a temp directory.\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 4.3: Trace ID Generation & Injection]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-dispatch]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#FR36-37 — Observability, trace ID injection]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR22 — Trace ID per iteration]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR36 — Trace IDs correlate across iteration, prompt, logs, metrics, traces]\n- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt, lines 14-15, 121-125]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState interface, TaskCheckpoint]\n- [Source: src/lib/session-manager.ts — immutable state pattern reference]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration.md — predecessor story]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md — predecessor story]\n","numLines":183,"startLine":1,"totalLines":183}}}
