{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CQ3WEDeg9gQYTmp1XUsmqf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019jkuAtUsjFDBxAmQrDhT2W","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Verify story 4-3 test-provable","prompt":"Verify story 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection using local CLI checks (test-provable tier).\n\nStory file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-3-trace-id-generation-injection.md\n\nThe project is at /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness — a TypeScript/Node.js project.\n\nExecute these steps and report results:\n1. Run `npm run build` in the project directory. Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n2. Run `npm run test:unit` in the project directory. Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n3. Run coverage check: `npx codeharness coverage --min-file 80` Report: coverage percentage per file.\n4. For each of the 9 ACs in the story file, verify it:\n\n   **AC 1:** File `src/lib/trace-id.ts` exists and exports `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string`\n   - Check: `ls src/lib/trace-id.ts` and `grep 'export.*generateTraceId' src/lib/trace-id.ts`\n\n   **AC 2:** `generateTraceId('abc123', 2, 'verify')` returns `'ch-abc123-2-verify'`\n   - Check: look in test file `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts` for a test that verifies this exact case, and confirm test passes.\n\n   **AC 3:** Special characters in runId are sanitized (spaces, slashes, unicode replaced with hyphens)\n   - Check: look for sanitization tests in the test file, confirm they pass.\n\n   **AC 4:** `formatTracePrompt(traceId)` returns a structured block with `[TRACE] trace_id=...`\n   - Check: `grep 'export.*formatTracePrompt' src/lib/trace-id.ts` and check test assertions.\n\n   **AC 5:** `formatTracePrompt` output works with `dispatchAgent()` via `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt`\n   - Check: `grep 'appendSystemPrompt' src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts` — confirm the option exists and is handled.\n\n   **AC 6:** `recordTraceId(traceId, state)` appends trace ID to `trace_ids: string[]` on WorkflowState\n   - Check: `grep 'export.*recordTraceId' src/lib/trace-id.ts` and check test file for immutability test.\n\n   **AC 7:** `readWorkflowState()` correctly deserializes `trace_ids` from YAML\n   - Check: look for round-trip persistence test in test file.\n\n   **AC 8:** Multiple iterations accumulate trace IDs in order\n   - Check: look for accumulation test in test file.\n\n   **AC 9:** Tests pass at 80%+ coverage for trace-id module\n   - Check: test output and coverage output from steps 1-3.\n\n5. Generate proof document at `verification/4-3-trace-id-generation-injection-proof.md` with evidence from each check. Use this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Proof: 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection\n\nStory: Trace ID Generation & Injection\nVerified: {timestamp}\nTier: test-provable\n\n## Build\n{PASS/FAIL + evidence}\n\n## Tests\n{PASS/FAIL + evidence}\n\n## Coverage\n{coverage data}\n\n## AC 1: Trace ID generator module exists\n**Verdict:** PASS/FAIL\n**Evidence:** {one-line evidence}\n\n## AC 2: Trace ID format correctness\n**Verdict:** PASS/FAIL\n**Evidence:** {one-line evidence}\n\n... (repeat for all 9 ACs)\n\n## Summary\n- Total ACs: 9\n- Passed: N\n- Failed: N\n- Escalated: 0\n```\n\n6. Run `npx codeharness verify --story 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection` to validate the proof format.\n7. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, missing files, unexpected behavior)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky or suboptimal)\n- Verification gaps (ACs that were hard to verify, weak evidence)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":180,"cache_read_input_tokens":47095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":180},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015-85c3-0be0521b6265","uuid":"68aa656d-d30c-4f36-88a2-d67e53c9b76d"}
