{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gu8BTgGy3Cdyu7or9r1h8v","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verification Proof: 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection\n2\t\n3\tStory: Trace ID Generation & Injection\n4\tVerified: 2026-04-03T01:00:00Z\n5\tTier: test-provable\n6\t\n7\t## Build\n8\t**PASS** — `npm run build` completed successfully via tsup (ESM + DTS builds, no errors).\n9\t\n10\t## Tests\n11\t**PASS** — 36/36 tests passed in `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts` (vitest, 13ms total test time).\n12\t\n13\t## Coverage\n14\t- `src/lib/trace-id.ts`: 100% Statements, 100% Branch, 100% Functions, 100% Lines (v8 coverage via vitest).\n15\t\n16\t## AC 1: Trace ID generator module exists\n17\t**Verdict:** PASS\n18\t**Evidence:** `src/lib/trace-id.ts` exists and exports `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` (line 31-45).\n19\t\n20\t## AC 2: Trace ID format correctness\n21\t**Verdict:** PASS\n22\t**Evidence:** Test `produces correct format for simple inputs` asserts `generateTraceId('abc123', 2, 'verify')` returns `'ch-abc123-2-verify'` — passes.\n23\t\n24\t## AC 3: Special character sanitization\n25\t**Verdict:** PASS\n26\t**Evidence:** 9 sanitization tests pass: spaces replaced with hyphens, slashes/backslashes sanitized, dots sanitized, unicode stripped, consecutive hyphens collapsed, leading/trailing hyphens trimmed.\n27\t\n28\t## AC 4: formatTracePrompt returns structured block\n29\t**Verdict:** PASS\n30\t**Evidence:** `formatTracePrompt` exported (line 54), returns `[TRACE] trace_id=...` block. Tests verify `[TRACE]` marker, `trace_id=` value, and instruction text — all pass.\n31\t\n32\t## AC 5: formatTracePrompt works with dispatchAgent appendSystemPrompt\n33\t**Verdict:** PASS\n34\t**Evidence:** `agent-dispatch.ts` line 15 declares `appendSystemPrompt?: string` in `DispatchOptions`; lines 123-124 append it to `definition.instructions`. Integration path confirmed.\n35\t\n36\t## AC 6: recordTraceId appends to trace_ids array\n37\t**Verdict:** PASS\n38\t**Evidence:** `recordTraceId` exported (line 69), test `appends trace ID to trace_ids array` passes. Immutability test `does not mutate the input state` passes.\n39\t\n40\t## AC 7: readWorkflowState deserializes trace_ids\n41\t**Verdict:** PASS\n42\t**Evidence:** Round-trip persistence test `write state with trace_ids, read it back, array matches` passes — writes 3 trace IDs via `writeWorkflowState`, reads back via `readWorkflowState`, asserts array equality.\n43\t\n44\t## AC 8: Multiple iterations accumulate trace IDs in order\n45\t**Verdict:** PASS\n46\t**Evidence:** Test `accumulates trace IDs in order across multiple calls` chains 3 `recordTraceId` calls and asserts order `['ch-run1-0-init', 'ch-run1-1-implement', 'ch-run1-2-verify']`. Persistence test `multiple recordTraceId calls persist correctly` confirms disk round-trip.\n47\t\n48\t## AC 9: 80%+ coverage for trace-id module\n49\t**Verdict:** PASS\n50\t**Evidence:** v8 coverage reports 100% across all metrics (Stmts, Branch, Funcs, Lines) for `trace-id.ts`. 36 tests cover: format correctness, sanitization, prompt formatting, state recording, immutability, round-trip persistence, and multi-iteration accumulation.\n51\t\n52\t## Summary\n53\t- Total ACs: 9\n54\t- Passed: 9\n55\t- Failed: 0\n56\t- Escalated: 0\n57\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015-85c3-0be0521b6265","uuid":"c4d33872-ad44-4e0a-bc89-aa5569098598","timestamp":"2026-04-02T20:58:40.268Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/4-3-trace-id-generation-injection-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection\n\nStory: Trace ID Generation & Injection\nVerified: 2026-04-03T01:00:00Z\nTier: test-provable\n\n## Build\n**PASS** — `npm run build` completed successfully via tsup (ESM + DTS builds, no errors).\n\n## Tests\n**PASS** — 36/36 tests passed in `src/lib/__tests__/trace-id.test.ts` (vitest, 13ms total test time).\n\n## Coverage\n- `src/lib/trace-id.ts`: 100% Statements, 100% Branch, 100% Functions, 100% Lines (v8 coverage via vitest).\n\n## AC 1: Trace ID generator module exists\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `src/lib/trace-id.ts` exists and exports `generateTraceId(runId: string, iteration: number, taskName: string): string` (line 31-45).\n\n## AC 2: Trace ID format correctness\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test `produces correct format for simple inputs` asserts `generateTraceId('abc123', 2, 'verify')` returns `'ch-abc123-2-verify'` — passes.\n\n## AC 3: Special character sanitization\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** 9 sanitization tests pass: spaces replaced with hyphens, slashes/backslashes sanitized, dots sanitized, unicode stripped, consecutive hyphens collapsed, leading/trailing hyphens trimmed.\n\n## AC 4: formatTracePrompt returns structured block\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `formatTracePrompt` exported (line 54), returns `[TRACE] trace_id=...` block. Tests verify `[TRACE]` marker, `trace_id=` value, and instruction text — all pass.\n\n## AC 5: formatTracePrompt works with dispatchAgent appendSystemPrompt\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `agent-dispatch.ts` line 15 declares `appendSystemPrompt?: string` in `DispatchOptions`; lines 123-124 append it to `definition.instructions`. Integration path confirmed.\n\n## AC 6: recordTraceId appends to trace_ids array\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** `recordTraceId` exported (line 69), test `appends trace ID to trace_ids array` passes. Immutability test `does not mutate the input state` passes.\n\n## AC 7: readWorkflowState deserializes trace_ids\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Round-trip persistence test `write state with trace_ids, read it back, array matches` passes — writes 3 trace IDs via `writeWorkflowState`, reads back via `readWorkflowState`, asserts array equality.\n\n## AC 8: Multiple iterations accumulate trace IDs in order\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Test `accumulates trace IDs in order across multiple calls` chains 3 `recordTraceId` calls and asserts order `['ch-run1-0-init', 'ch-run1-1-implement', 'ch-run1-2-verify']`. Persistence test `multiple recordTraceId calls persist correctly` confirms disk round-trip.\n\n## AC 9: 80%+ coverage for trace-id module\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:** v8 coverage reports 100% across all metrics (Stmts, Branch, Funcs, Lines) for `trace-id.ts`. 36 tests cover: format correctness, sanitization, prompt formatting, state recording, immutability, round-trip persistence, and multi-iteration accumulation.\n\n## Summary\n- Total ACs: 9\n- Passed: 9\n- Failed: 0\n- Escalated: 0\n","numLines":57,"startLine":1,"totalLines":57}}}
