{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0179srkeUKnTdvBYz6XFcrPA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XJqrzG7PE3BA8RK83xTvFP","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md","limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4779,"cache_read_input_tokens":27550,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4779,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CbLWtVmWF61E7hNafuWso7","session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015-85c3-0be0521b6265","uuid":"775d8f2e-9de9-427c-a9be-ae0447b0e52e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XJqrzG7PE3BA8RK83xTvFP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n3\tlastStep: 8\n4\tstatus: 'complete'\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-02'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd-evaluator-redesign.md\n8\t  - research/domain-harness-design-long-running-agents-research-2026-04-01.md\n9\t  - research/technical-ai-agent-verification-testing-research-2026-03-16.md\n10\t  - research/technical-workflow-engine-implementation-research-2026-04-02.md\n11\t  - architecture.md (v1 architecture, brownfield context)\n12\tworkflowType: 'architecture'\n13\tproject_name: 'codeharness'\n14\tuser_name: 'BMad'\n15\tdate: '2026-04-02'\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t# Architecture Decision Document\n19\t\n20\t_This document builds collaboratively through step-by-step discovery. Sections are appended as we work through each architectural decision together._\n21\t\n22\t## Project Context Analysis\n23\t\n24\t### Requirements Overview\n25\t\n26\t**Functional Requirements:** 43 FRs across 10 capability areas — Workflow Definition (6), Agent Configuration (6), Workflow Configuration (3), Workflow Execution (8), Adversarial Verification (5), Feedback Loop (3), Circuit Breaker (4), Observability (2), CLI Commands (4), Legacy Removal (2).\n27\t\n28\t**Non-Functional Requirements:** 18 NFRs across Performance (5), Reliability (5), Integration (4), Code Quality (4). Architecture-critical NFRs: crash recovery via state persistence (NFR6-8), programmatic agent dispatch only (NFR11), optional observability (NFR14).\n29\t\n30\t**Scale & Complexity:**\n31\t- Primary domain: Developer tooling (CLI + plugin)\n32\t- Complexity level: High\n33\t- Estimated architectural components: ~10\n34\t- Cross-cutting concerns: config resolution chain, trace ID propagation, crash recovery, evaluator isolation\n35\t\n36\t### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37\t\n38\t- Runtime: Node.js (TypeScript)\n39\t- Dependencies: `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n40\t- Execution substrate: Agent SDK `query()` — async generator, session management, JSON schema output\n41\t- State: Single `workflow-state.yaml` in repo (beads-level simplicity)\n42\t- Evaluator isolation: Separate workspace, no source code, Docker container for artifact\n43\t- Docker: Required for evaluator but graceful degradation if missing (Journey 5)\n44\t\n45\t### Cross-Cutting Concerns\n46\t\n47\t1. **Config resolution** — every agent/workflow dispatch resolves embedded → user → project patches\n48\t2. **Trace ID propagation** — generated per iteration, injected into agent prompts, correlates to observability\n49\t3. **Crash recovery** — state persisted after each task, engine resumes from last checkpoint\n50\t4. **Evaluator isolation** — separate workspace, `disallowedTools` enforcement, `source_access: false`\n51\t\n52\t## Starter Template Evaluation\n53\t\n54\t### Primary Technology Domain\n55\t\n56\tCLI developer tool — Node.js/TypeScript. Brownfield project with established toolchain.\n57\t\n58\t### Starter Options: Not Applicable (Brownfield)\n59\t\n60\tExisting project toolchain is retained:\n61\t\n62\t| Decision | Current (Keep) | Source |\n63\t|----------|---------------|--------|\n64\t| Language | TypeScript (strict) | Existing project |\n65\t| Build | tsup | Existing project |\n66\t| Test | vitest (unit) + BATS (integration) | Existing project |\n67\t| CLI | commander | Existing project |\n68\t| YAML | yaml package | Existing project |\n69\t| **New** | @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk | Research — replaces bash spawn |\n70\t\n71\t**No starter template needed.** One new dependency added. Internals reworked.\n72\t\n73\t## Core Architectural Decisions\n74\t\n75\t### Decision Priority Analysis\n76\t\n77\t**Critical Decisions (Block Implementation):**\n78\t1. Module boundaries — what code goes where\n79\t2. Evaluator workspace isolation — how to enforce source-free verification\n80\t3. Evaluator verdict schema — the contract between evaluator and engine\n81\t\n82\t**Important Decisions (Shape Architecture):**\n83\t4. Embedded template storage — where agent/workflow YAML files live in the package\n84\t5. Config resolution caching — resolve once or every dispatch\n85\t\n86\t**Deferred Decisions (Post-MVP):**\n87\t- PersonaNexus trait compilation algorithm (Growth phase)\n88\t- Pluggable evaluator strategies interface (Growth phase)\n89\t- Workflow marketplace format/registry (Vision phase)\n90\t\n91\t### AD1: Module Boundaries\n92\t\n93\t| Module | Responsibility | Key FRs |\n94\t|--------|---------------|---------|\n95\t| `workflow-parser` | Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded→user→project) | FR1-6, FR13-15 |\n96\t| `agent-resolver` | Resolve agent config through patch chain, compile to SDK inline subagent definition | FR7-12 |\n97\t| `workflow-engine` | Execute flow steps, manage iterations, handle `loop:` blocks, inject evaluator findings into retries | FR16-18, FR29-31 |\n98\t| `agent-dispatch` | Call Agent SDK `query()`, manage sessions (fresh/continue), inject trace IDs | FR19-23 |\n99\t| `evaluator` | Blind evaluator workspace setup, spawn, JSON verdict parsing | FR24-28 |\n100\t| `circuit-breaker` | Score-based stagnation detection, score history tracking | FR32-35 |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CbLWtVmWF61E7hNafuWso7","session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015-85c3-0be0521b6265","uuid":"91883443-cf75-4b14-8223-9598a1cbc94a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:13:47.106Z"}
