{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016VHKytFCmN6FUa3CVJara9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement.md\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 4 Medium, 2 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 2 High, 4 Medium (all HIGH and MEDIUM fixed)\n\n**HIGH issues fixed:**\n1. **Path traversal via runId injection** — `runId` was interpolated directly into `/tmp/codeharness-verify-${runId}` with no sanitization. Added `sanitizeRunId()` that strips non-alphanumeric characters and leading dots.\n2. **Story file name collision** — Two files with the same `basename()` in different directories would silently overwrite each other. Added `deduplicateFilename()` that appends `-N` suffix on collision.\n\n**MEDIUM issues fixed:**\n3. **No test for runId edge cases** — Added 4 tests: path traversal chars, special chars, empty-after-sanitization, valid chars preserved.\n4. **Stale workspace leak** — Pre-existing workspace from crashed runs would contaminate new workspace. Added `rmSync` cleanup before creating directories. Added test.\n5. **Test runId collision across test runs** — Tests use fixed runIds; on test failure the workspace persists. Now moot since workspaces are cleaned before creation.\n6. **Missing test for toDispatchOptions return shape** — Added test verifying only `cwd` property exists.\n\n**Coverage result:** `source-isolation.ts` at 100% all metrics. Overall project: 96.72%, all 157 files above 80%.\n\n**Story status:** Updated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Path traversal vulnerability in `runId` — unsanitized user input used in file path construction (FIXED)\n- HIGH: Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss when two story files share a name (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Stale workspace contamination from crashed previous runs (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Missing edge case tests for sanitization, deduplication, return shape (FIXED)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- The `deduplicateFilename` counter loop is unbounded — theoretically loops forever if filenames `stem-1` through `stem-N` all exist. Extremely unlikely in practice (would need thousands of identically-named story files). Tech debt.\n- The module hardcodes `/tmp/` as the base path. On some systems (e.g., containerized environments), `/tmp` may not exist or may have restricted permissions. A configurable base path would be more robust. Low priority since AD2 explicitly chose `/tmp` for simplicity.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None for `source-isolation.ts` (100% all metrics).\n- No integration test verifying that `dispatchAgent()` actually receives and uses the `cwd` from `toDispatchOptions()` — would require SDK mocking. This is documented as an existing integration point verified by code inspection (AC #8).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module is correctly stateless, standalone, and follows existing patterns.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run ... --coverage` full output (~80 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~30 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~16 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: One unnecessary `readdirSync` import added then removed in source-isolation.ts (caught in same pass). Two test expectation corrections needed for sanitization output (could have traced the logic before writing the first test assertion)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: add2a6833d69cf50c (use SendMessage with to: 'add2a6833d69cf50c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54815\ntool_uses: 39\nduration_ms: 235251</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d3ed03d-179a-4015