e.g., containerized environments), `/tmp` may not exist or may have restricted permissions. A configurable base path would be more robust. Low priority since AD2 explicitly chose `/tmp` for simplicity.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None for `source-isolation.ts` (100% all metrics).\n- No integration test verifying that `dispatchAgent()` actually receives and uses the `cwd` from `toDispatchOptions()` — would require SDK mocking. This is documented as an existing integration point verified by code inspection (AC #8).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module is correctly stateless, standalone, and follows existing patterns.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this review.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run ... --coverage` full output (~80 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~30 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~16 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: One unnecessary `readdirSync` import added then removed in source-isolation.ts (caught in same pass). Two test expectation corrections needed for sanitization output (could have traced the logic before writing the first test assertion)."}],"totalDurationMs":235251,"totalTokens":54815,"totalToolUseCount":39,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":235,"cache_read_input_tokens":53629,"output_tokens":950,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":235},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
