e-id-generation-injection — dev-story (2026-04-03T00:30)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Write: 2, Bash: 4, Glob: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — code-review (2026-04-03T00:37)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `formatTracePrompt('')` silently produced empty trace marker. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor. Fixed with 10 new tests.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):** duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — verification (2026-04-03T00:55)\n\n- **`npx codeharness verify` fails** due to stale `AGENTS.md` — wants documentation for new modules in `src/lib/` (agent-dispatch.ts, agent-resolver.ts, session-manager.ts, trace-id.ts). Documentation debt, not a story 4-3 issue.\n- Build, tests (36/36), and coverage (100% trace-id.ts) all clean.\n- All 9 ACs verified with evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: test:unit run (~50 lines), trace-id verbose test (~40 lines), coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: codeharness verify called twice\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — create-story (2026-04-03T01:05)\n\n- **Risk:** AC #4 depends on `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` having `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` from story 3-2. Not verified that template exists.\n- `/tmp/` path pattern is Unix-specific. Not a concern on darwin but noted for portability.\n- All 9 ACs are test-provable (pure file system operations testable with real temp dirs).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Read: 